&\phantom{=}f'(x)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}\sqrt[3]{x^2-2x+8}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}\sqrt[3]{u(x)}&&\gray{\text{Let }u(x)=x^2-2x+8}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{3}[u(x)]^{^{-\scriptsize\dfrac{2}{3}}}u'(x)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{3}[x^2-2x+8]^{^{-\scriptsize\dfrac{2}{3}}}(2x-2)&&\gray{\text{Substitute }u(x)\text{ back}}
\end{align}$

